27/04/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The IMF and the government have reached an agreement on extending a loan to Romania, Finance Minister Mihai Tanasescu said Monday (26 April) after returning from talks in Washington.
The agreement includes a two-year precautionary stand-by agreement, under which Romania could borrow up to $362m in case of emergency.
(Rompres, Nine o'Clock - 26/04/04)
